    "element_subtype": "standard-indented",
    "content": "The eighth commandment condemns ... theft and robbery. It demands strict integrity in the minutest details of the affairs of life. It forbids overreaching in trade and requires the payment of just debts or wages.&rdquo;<sup class=\"chapterendnote\"><a class=\"chapterendnote\">2<span class=\"chapterendnote\"><span class=\"egwlink egwlink_book\" title=\"PP 309.1\" data-link=\"84.1369\">Patriarchs and Prophets, 309</span>.</span></a></sup>",
