    "element_type": "p",
    "element_subtype": "standard-indented",
    "content": "<strong>Danger in Extreme Positions</strong>&mdash;Some are not discreet and would incur debts that might be avoided. Others exercise a caution that savors of unbelief. By taking advantage of circumstances we may at times invest means to such advantage that the work of God will be strengthened and upbuilt, and yet keep strictly to right principles.<sup class=\"chapterendnote\"><a class=\"chapterendnote\">12<span class=\"chapterendnote\"><span class=\"egwlink egwlink_book\" title=\"Ms 20, 1891\" data-link=\"14057.7257001\">Manuscript 20, 1891</span>.</span></a></sup>",
